@node Requirements
@section Requirements

@noindent
@code{AWS} has been mainly developed with @code{GNAT} on Windows NT
and built and tested many times on @code{GNU/Linux}, it should be fairly
portable across platforms. To build @code{AWS} you need:

@itemize @bullet

@item GNU/Ada (GNAT compiler) ;
@cindex GNAT
@cindex GNU/Ada

@code{AWS} uses some @code{GNAT} specific packages and we have no plan
to support another compiler at this point. It is too much work for us
to check if @code{AWS} compiles to other compilers anyway. To build
this version you need at least @code{GNAT 3.15}. On Windows you must also
install @code{GNATWin} (Windows specific package).

@item a socket binding (@b{optional}) ;
@cindex socket binding

@code{GNAT.Sockets} is the default socket implementation used. It is possible
to use @code{AdaSockets} (@code{AdaSockets} was used in AWS v 1.2) and
in this case you must install the @code{AdaSockets} package.

On Windows you must use the one distributed at @*
@url{http://perso.wanadoo.fr/pascal.obry/contrib.html} which is a
Win32 port (done by Dmitriy Anisimkov) of the ENST version.

On UNIX you must use the socket binding from ENST @*
@url{http://www.rfc1149.net/devel/adasockets}.

@item a POSIX binding - Interface to the underlying OS services (@b{optional}) ;
@cindex POSIX

On Windows you can use the one distributed at: 
@url{http://perso.wanadoo.fr/pascal.obry}. On UNIX look for the 
Florist package at @url{http://www.cs.fsu.edu/~baker/florist.html}.

@item OpenSSL (@b{optional}) ;
@cindex OpenSSL

OpenSSL is an Open Source toolkit implementing the @i{Secure Sockets Layer}
(SSL v2 and v3) and much more. You'll find libraries for Win32 into this
distribution. For other platforms just download the OpenSSL source
distribution from @url{http://www.openssl.org} and build it.

@item OpenLDAP (@b{optional}) ;
@cindex OpenLDAP

OpenLDAP is an Open Source toolkit implementing the 
@i{Lightweight Directory Access Protocol}.
If you want to use the @code{AWS/LDAP} API
on UNIX based systems, you need to install properly the @code{OpenLDAP}
package. On Windows you don't need to install it as the
@file{libldap.a} library will be built by @code{AWS} and will use the
standard Windows @code{LDAP DLL} @file{wldap32.dll}.

You can download OpenLDAP from @url{http://www.openldap.org}.

@end itemize

@c ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node AWS.OS_Lib
@section AWS.OS_Lib
@cindex AWS.OS_Lib

@noindent
The @code{AWS.OS_Lib} has 3 implementations. One using @code{POSIX}, one using
@code{GNAT.OS_Lib} and one using direct @code{Win32} calls. This last
one is not anymore supported in this version. Contribution is welcome
of course.

@table @b

@item GNAT.OS_Lib implementation

Version using @code{GNAT.OS_Lib} is GNAT dependent and will run on whatever
OS GNAT has be ported to. This is the @b{default implementation} used.

@smallexample
@cartouche
@group
$ make gnat_oslib
@end group
@end cartouche
@end smallexample

@item POSIX implementation

Version with @code{POSIX} is compiler and OS independent (well if you
have a @code{POSIX} implementation for your OS). Check out @code{Florist}
which is available on many @code{UNIX} and the version for Win32 is
available on @url{http://perso.wanadoo.fr/pascal.obry/contrib.html}.

@smallexample
@cartouche
@group
$ make posix_oslib
@end group
@end cartouche
@end smallexample

@item Win32 implementation (not anymore supported)

Version for Win32 should be usable by any Ada compiler for Windows 
95/98/NT/2000/XP.

@smallexample
@cartouche
@group
$ make win32_oslib
@end group
@end cartouche
@end smallexample

@end table

@c ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node AWS.Net.Std
@section AWS.Net.Std
@cindex AWS.Net.Std

@noindent
This package is the standard (non-SSL) socket implementation. It exists
different implementation of this package:

@table @b

@item GNAT implementation

Version based on @code{GNAT.Sockets}, is @code{GNAT} dependent and will
run on whatever OS @code{GNAT} has be ported to. This is the 
@b{default implementation} used. To select this implementation just do:

@smallexample
@cartouche
@group
$ make gnatsockets
@end group
@end cartouche
@end smallexample

@item AdaSockets implementation

Version using @code{AdaSockets} packages. This was the default implementation
used up to AWS 1.2. To select this implementation just do:

@smallexample
@cartouche
@group
$ make adasockets
@end group
@end cartouche
@end smallexample

@end table

